data.name: AboutExpire
data.value: The certificate is about to expire.

data.name: CertificateNotFound
data.value: Requested endpoint does not provide SSL/TLS certificate.

data.name: CtlNotSignatureValid
data.value: A CTL used to create this chain did not have a valid signature.

data.name: CtlNotTimeValid
data.value: A certificate trust list (CTL) used to create this chain was not time valid.

data.name: CtlNotValidForUsage
data.value: A CTL used to create this chain is not valid for this usage.

data.name: Cyclic
data.value: The certificate was issued by a certification authority that the original certificate had certified.

data.name: ExplicitDistrust
data.value: The certificate is explicitly distrusted.

data.name: HasExcludedNameConstraint
data.value: The certificate has a name constraints extension, and one of the name choices in the end certificate is explicitly excluded.

data.name: HasNotDefinedNameConstraint
data.value: The certificate has a name constraints extension and a name constraint is missing for one of the name choices in the end certificate.

data.name: HasNotPermittedNameConstraint
data.value: The certificate has a name constraints extension, and there is not a permitted name constraint for one of the name choices in the end certificate.

data.name: HasNotSupportedCriticalExtension
data.value: The certificate does not support a critical extension.

data.name: HasNotSupportedNameConstraint
data.value: The certificate has a name constraints extension that contains unsupported fields.

data.name: HasWeakSignature
data.value: The certificate has not been strong signed.

data.name: InvalidBasicConstraints
data.value: The certificate has a basic constraints extension, and either the certificate cannot be used to issue other certificates, or the chain path length has been exceeded.

data.name: InvalidExtension
data.value: The certificate has an extension that is not valid.

data.name: InvalidNameConstraints
data.value: The certificate has a name constraints extension that is not valid.

data.name: InvalidPolicyConstraints
data.value: The certificate ohas a policy constraints extension, and one of the issued certificates has a disallowed policy mapping extension or does not have a required issuance policies extension.

data.name: MissingAltNameExtension
data.value: Subject Alternative Name extension is not presented in certificate.

data.name: NameMismatch
data.value: The certificate presented by endpoint was issued for a different website's address.

data.name: NoError
data.value: No error found for this certificate or chain.

data.name: NoIssuanceChainPolicy
data.value: The end certificate does not have any resultant issuance policies, and one of the issuing certification authority certificates has a policy constraints extension requiring it.

data.name: NotInTransparencyLog
data.value: The certificate is not published in Certificate Transparency Log

data.name: NotSignatureValid
data.value: The certificate does not have a valid signature.

data.name: NotTimeNested
data.value: The certificate validity is not nested within issuer validity.

data.name: NotTimeValid
data.value: The certificate is not time valid.

data.name: NotValidForUsage
data.value: The certificate is not valid for its proposed usage.

data.name: OfflineRevocation
data.value: The revocation function was unable to check revocation because the revocation server was offline.

data.name: PartialChain
data.value: The certificate chain is not complete.

data.name: RevocationStatusUnknown
data.value: The revocation function was unable to check revocation for the certificate.

data.name: Revoked
data.value: The certificate is revoked.

data.name: TooLongValidity
data.value: Certificate validity exceeds CAB/Forum or Internet PKI standards.

data.name: UntrustedRoot
data.value: The certificate and its chain is based on an untrusted root.

data.name: WeakRsaPublicKey
data.value: The certificate uses weak RSA asymmetric key.
